,0.08899,0.092471,0.09431,0.09403,0.094888,0.092605,0.092177,0.079628,0.062384]},{"section":10,"text":"Bitemporal hemianopia is classic for a pituitary tumor compressing the optic chiasm.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036153,0.078051,0.089483,0.096112,0.097122,0.098374,0.097256,0.091722,0.094233,0.082117,0.073002,0.066376],"unified_progress":[0.044717,0.070302,0.087434,0.099761,0.10196,0.10263,0.098974,0.093926,0.094487,0.080116,0.067652,0.058039]},{"section":11,"text":"However, the case says \"bitemporal superior quadrantanopia.\"","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046349,0.08619,0.089188,0.091135,0.091824,0.093916,0.092925,0.090874,0.090988,0.082516,0.075325,0.06877],"unified_progress":[0.053012,0.076653,0.086702,0.094145,0.098605,0.097864,0.09616,0.093531,0.091371,0.0815,0.070606,0.059851]},{"section":12,"text":"That still fits with a lesion at the optic chiasm, like a pituitary adenoma.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03534,0.077597,0.090892,0.098207,0.097433,0.097535,0.096084,0.089569,0.096143,0.081697,0.071752,0.06775],"unified_progress":[0.03703,0.068955,0.088979,0.10191,0.10624,0.10386,0.10053,0.093414,0.095684,0.078365,0.066364,0.058667]},{"section":13,"text":"Optic atrophy could be due to chronic compression affecting the optic nerves, leading to damage over time.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030385,0.068895,0.081792,0.091212,0.095887,0.099667,0.10103,0.096354,0.097223,0.087772,0.079372,0.070411],"unified_progress":[0.043958,0.062638,0.077786,0.088916,0.096948,0.099416,0.099428,0.097476,0.097765,0.08864,0.079458,0.06757]},{"section":14,"text":"Putting it together: a pituitary adenoma, specifically a prolactinoma, which is a type of microadenoma or macroadenoma.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03228,0.066099,0.078018,0.088049,0.093651,0.096467,0.097921,0.094031,0.092705,0.090205,0.08